n <- length(x)
beta <- .03

mu

s <- grf(grid=cp, cov.pars=c(2, 3))$data
## grf: simulation on a set of locations provided by the user
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=2, phi=3)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
mu <- exp(s)
y <- rpois(100, lam=mu)
plot(cp, asp=1, type="n")
text(cp[,1], cp[,2], y, cex=2)

set.seed(23)
S <- grf(100, cov.pars=c(1, 0.25))
## grf: simulation(s) on randomly chosen locations with  100  points
## grf: process with  1  covariance structure(s)
## grf: nugget effect is: tausq= 0 
## grf: covariance model 1 is: exponential(sigmasq=1, phi=0.25)
## grf: decomposition algorithm used is:  cholesky 
## grf: End of simulation procedure. Number of realizations: 1
S1 <- S
S1$data <- exp(S$data)
set.seed(351)
y1 <- rpois(100, lam=S1$data)

points(S1)
text(S1$coords, lab=y1, col=4,pos=4, offset=0.3)

S2 <- S
S2$data <- exp(1 + S$data)
set.seed(351)
y2 <- rpois(100, lam=S2$data)

points(S2)
text(S2$coords, lab=y2, col=4,pos=4, offset=0.3)

S3 <- S
err <- rnorm(100, sd=0.1)
